description:
[LinuxVDI][Disconnect]disconnect will not logoff is it arrives after another startSession

disconnect process
after agent receive ‘notifyVNCDisconnection’ message from mks
agent will start the disconnect process.
if disconnectTimeout confined in broker is not never, at the end of disconnect process, agent will startLogOffSessionTimer.

startSession process
a) 
do sth
stopPendingSessionTimer();
stopLogoffSessionTimer();
b) do sth
c) startPendingSessionTimer();

If disconnect session timeout, disconnect process comes in b before c.
Then after c, we will get a logOffTimer and a pendingSessionTimer.
add additional stopLogoffSessionTimer() before startPendingSessionTimer() in c.
Also, in disconnect callback we check the vuath.
If the vauth token is not the latest one, means a new session already
started. For this kind of case, we will not start logoff timer

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: local test done on u1804
Documentation Notes: 
Bug Number: 2347885
Reviewed by: ksong
Approved by: ksong
Mailto: 
Review URL:
title: [LinuxVDI][Disconnect]disconnect will not logoff is it arrives after another startSession

description:
[Mac Client] Fix bug 2292813 and 2344615

Bug 2292813: [Mojave/Mac client Dark mode Support]Desktop display is a little fuzzy with Normal display
Root cause: The bilinear filter in metal script blurs the display.
Root cause: MTKView cannot fire a callback to update the render view before paint, which is different from the callback "prepareOpenGL" for NSOpenGLView, and it will cause the windowID and surfaceID failed to send to the mks to define the swbwindow, which will block the rendering.
Solution: Disable the bilinear filter for the metal rendering and use nearest filter instead and always return the pixel scale 1 if "wantsBestResolutionOpenGLSurface" is not set to avoid scale the iosurface size unnecessarily according to
title: [Mac Client] Fix bug 2292813 and 2344615

description:
[HTML5VideoPlayer] Fix an issue where the player never quits

We install the SimpleTask in the OnAfterCreated callback.
It can happen that the callback is not fired when
the parent window gets invalid quickly. This causes the player
to never quit.

The changelist fixes the issue by adding the SimpleTask
installation to the constructor instead of the OnAfterCreated
callback.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done:
Added rdeLibs logging to the player. I launched a desktop
and killed the vmware-remotemks.exe process quickly enough
such that OnAfterCreated is never fired. Verified that
the issue is fixed.
Documentation Notes: 
Bug Number: 2345545
Reviewed by: joeqiux
Approved by: 
Mailto: 
Review URL:
title: [HTML5VideoPlayer] Fix an issue where the player never quits

description:
[hcwin]Fix bug 2339044- installShortcutsThenQuit command line should not install duplicated shortcuts
[Root cause]:
Win client does not always save the shortcut into prefs immediately when there is category change during the session, such as refresh of launch items. A second Win client will update the shortcuts based on the prefs, in some case dup shortcuts may be created due to inconsistency between prefs and shortcuts created in disk.
[Solution]:
Save prefs immediately when shortcuts updated.
QA Notes: 
Testing Done:
Tested sandbox
title: [hcwin]Fix bug 2339044- installShortcutsThenQuit command line should not install duplicated shortcuts

description:
Fix bug 2341849:Out of bounds read which could lead to priv escallation
Passthru server is a rpc server to communicate between agent and client on same host to support nested scenarios.
Both agent and client have a passthru server and each acts both server and client role to communicate each other.
But it did not provide AuthCallback to provide security protecttion.
In this patch:
1. AuthCallback is provided. server only accepts requests from authenticated user.
2. In the interface, check the passed in buffer length.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done:
title: Fix bug 2341849:Out of bounds read which could lead to priv escallation

description:
Fix bug 2339413: On nested mode, default printer on Agent is not consistent with the one on Client

If  "Let Windows to manager my default printer" is enabled. SetDefaultPrinter() may not work.
Solution:
Under current user scope,when print server start, we disable "Let Windows to manager my default printe".
When print server start, restore the original setting.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done:
title: Fix bug 2339413: On nested mode, default printer on Agent is not consistent with the one on Client

description:
[UWP rdeSvc] implement simplest AppSvc interface to make App Session enter Unity

For VM Hosted App session, we need the session enter unity to hide Taskbar/Desktop icons, currently rdeSvc client in UWP client doesn't implement use unitySvc or AppSvc. This patch implements the simplest AppSvc interface  to notify the session type for AppSvcm and make app session enter unity, so for VM Hosted App session we could hide taskbar/desktop icons.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: hcwin10uwp:
title: [UWP rdeSvc] implement simplest AppSvc interface to make App Session enter Unity

description:
[Win10 UWP Client] Fix mobilelibs auto bump failed issue

Root cause:
Recently some changes are made which changed the check rule for some macro which is leading build error for hcwin10uwp with latest mobilelibs

Solution:
Remove the dependency of INCLDE_ALLOW_MKS and COREMKS for UWP client, this won't have side effects on hcwin10uwp since we don't use these marcos in client code.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: sandbox (linked latest mobilelibs build):
title: [Win10 UWP Client] Fix mobilelibs auto bump failed issue

description:
[Mac Client] Fix a macOS 10.14 issue for the UI of the selective multiple  monitors.

Apple's macOS 10.14 changed the NSButton border style to remove the border. Looks that this is not officially announced. Maybe this is a bug, maybe not. Whatever, the Settings UI for selective multiple monitors is not fine, for both desktop settings and RDSH app settings.

Solution:
Draw the border of the monitor button manually.
1) Leave a white edge for 1 pixel. This is the seperator of adjacent monitor buttons.
2) Draw a dark gray border for each monitor buttons. The border width is 1 pixel.
3) Draw the monitor button color inside the border.

This change works for both desktop settings and RDSH app settings.

Note:
The codes of desktop settings and RDSH app settings will be merged in the future.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: locally. See the snapshot.
title: [Mac Client] Fix a macOS 10.14 issue for the UI of the selective multiple  monitors.

This patch is used to handle the notification from WinCDK, and notify the partner app according to the app advised event version.

The WinCDK side changes is already done. (

description:
Exclude KeyVault and KeyVaultCNG registry keys while exporting registry for DCT collection.

KeyVault and KeyVaultCNG keys contain sensitive data and are not exportable even by administrator. When DCT collection fails to export these registry keys, it prints warning messages. These warning messages(for KeyVault and KeyVaultCNG) are not useful and might confuse the user. So, this CLN contains the changes to exclude these sensitive keys while exporting the registry so that warning messages are printed for these keys.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: Tested with the SB that KeyVaultCNG is not exported and no warning message is printed.
Documentation Notes: 
Bug Number: 2316711
Reviewed by: vimalg, gpragyakail, pgreen
Approved by: 
Mailto: 
Review URL:
title: Exclude KeyVault and KeyVaultCNG registry keys while exporting registry for DCT collection.

description:
[Remote Experience][CDR][iOS Client] Fix bug 2315689 - UI Option "File sharing" is not hidden when agent disables CDR

Issue
When CDR is disabled in agent side, the in-session settings still shows the CDR option, this is different from other clients.

Root Cause
The in-session settings can not be updated according to CDR client and agent capability negotiation after session connected.

Solution
Record the result of CDR client and agent capability negotiation after session connected, and update the in-session settings according to it

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: 
hcios
title: [Remote Experience][CDR][iOS Client] Fix bug 2315689 - UI Option "File sharing" is not hidden when agent disables CDR

description:
[DPM-3230][hcwin]Unregister all file handlers before register new file handlers to make sure the removed entitlements disappear from the open with menu

Problem:
The file association handlers for the removed entitlements still exist in the open with popup menu.

Solution:
Using synchrounsly merging for App Management mode.
And remove the old file association handlers before registering new ones.

description:
[LinuxVDI][Disconnect]disconnect will not logoff is it arrives after another startSession

disconnect process
after agent receive ‘notifyVNCDisconnection’ message from mks
agent will start the disconnect process.
if disconnectTimeout confined in broker is not never, at the end of disconnect process, agent will startLogOffSessionTimer.

startSession process
a) 
do sth
stopPendingSessionTimer();
stopLogoffSessionTimer();
b) do sth
c) startPendingSessionTimer();

If disconnect session timeout, disconnect process comes in b before c.
Then after c, we will get a logOffTimer and a pendingSessionTimer.
add additional stopLogoffSessionTimer() before startPendingSessionTimer() in c.
Also, in disconnect callback we check the vuath.
If the vauth token is not the latest one, means a new session already
started. For this kind of case, we will not start logoff timer

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: local test done on u1804
Documentation Notes: 
Bug Number: 2347885
Reviewed by: ksong
Approved by: ksong
Mailto: 
Review URL:
title: [LinuxVDI][Disconnect]disconnect will not logoff is it arrives after another startSession

description:
[Mac Client] Fix bug 2292813 and 2344615

Bug 2292813: [Mojave/Mac client Dark mode Support]Desktop display is a little fuzzy with Normal display
Root cause: The bilinear filter in metal script blurs the display.
Root cause: MTKView cannot fire a callback to update the render view before paint, which is different from the callback "prepareOpenGL" for NSOpenGLView, and it will cause the windowID and surfaceID failed to send to the mks to define the swbwindow, which will block the rendering.
Solution: Disable the bilinear filter for the metal rendering and use nearest filter instead and always return the pixel scale 1 if "wantsBestResolutionOpenGLSurface" is not set to avoid scale the iosurface size unnecessarily according to
title: [Mac Client] Fix bug 2292813 and 2344615

description:
[HTML5VideoPlayer] Fix an issue where the player never quits

We install the SimpleTask in the OnAfterCreated callback.
It can happen that the callback is not fired when
the parent window gets invalid quickly. This causes the player
to never quit.

The changelist fixes the issue by adding the SimpleTask
installation to the constructor instead of the OnAfterCreated
callback.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done:
Added rdeLibs logging to the player. I launched a desktop
and killed the vmware-remotemks.exe process quickly enough
such that OnAfterCreated is never fired. Verified that
the issue is fixed.
Documentation Notes:

description:
[hcwin]Fix bug 2339044- installShortcutsThenQuit command line should not install duplicated shortcuts
[Root cause]:
Win client does not always save the shortcut into prefs immediately when there is category change during the session, such as refresh of launch items. A second Win client will update the shortcuts based on the prefs, in some case dup shortcuts may be created due to inconsistency between prefs and shortcuts created in disk.
[Solution]:
Save prefs immediately when shortcuts updated.
QA Notes: 
Testing Done:
Tested sandbox
title: [hcwin]Fix bug 2339044- installShortcutsThenQuit command line should not install duplicated shortcuts

description:
Fix bug 2341849:Out of bounds read which could lead to priv escallation
Passthru server is a rpc server to communicate between agent and client on same host to support nested scenarios.
Both agent and client have a passthru server and each acts both server and client role to communicate each other.
But it did not provide AuthCallback to provide security protecttion.
In this patch:
1. AuthCallback is provided. server only accepts requests from authenticated user.
2. In the interface, check the passed in buffer length.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done:
title: Fix bug 2341849:Out of bounds read which could lead to priv escallation

description:
Fix bug 2339413: On nested mode, default printer on Agent is not consistent with the one on Client

If  "Let Windows to manager my default printer" is enabled. SetDefaultPrinter() may not work.
Solution:
Under current user scope,when print server start, we disable "Let Windows to manager my default printe".
When print server start, restore the original setting.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done:

description:
[UWP rdeSvc] implement simplest AppSvc interface to make App Session enter Unity

For VM Hosted App session, we need the session enter unity to hide Taskbar/Desktop icons, currently rdeSvc client in UWP client doesn't implement use unitySvc or AppSvc. This patch implements the simplest AppSvc interface  to notify the session type for AppSvcm and make app session enter unity, so for VM Hosted App session we could hide taskbar/desktop icons.

Testing Done: hcwin10uwp:
title: [UWP rdeSvc] implement simplest AppSvc interface to make App Session enter Unity

description:
[Mac Client] Fix a macOS 10.14 issue for the UI of the selective multiple  monitors.

Apple's macOS 10.14 changed the NSButton border style to remove the border. Looks that this is not officially announced. Maybe this is a bug, maybe not. Whatever, the Settings UI for selective multiple monitors is not fine, for both desktop settings and RDSH app settings.

Solution:
Draw the border of the monitor button manually.
1) Leave a white edge for 1 pixel. This is the seperator of adjacent monitor buttons.
2) Draw a dark gray border for each monitor buttons. The border width is 1 pixel.
3) Draw the monitor button color inside the border.

This change works for both desktop settings and RDSH app settings.

Note:
The codes of desktop settings and RDSH app settings will be merged in the future.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: locally. See the snapshot.
title: [Mac Client] Fix a macOS 10.14 issue for the UI of the selective multiple  monitors.

description:
Exclude KeyVault and KeyVaultCNG registry keys while exporting registry for DCT collection.

KeyVault and KeyVaultCNG keys contain sensitive data and are not exportable even by administrator. When DCT collection fails to export these registry keys, it prints warning messages. These warning messages(for KeyVault and KeyVaultCNG) are not useful and might confuse the user. So, this CLN contains the changes to exclude these sensitive keys while exporting the registry so that warning messages are printed for these keys.

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: Tested with the SB that KeyVaultCNG is not exported and no warning message is printed.
Documentation Notes: 
Bug Number: 2316711
Reviewed by: vimalg, gpragyakail, pgreen
Approved by: 
Mailto: 
Review URL:
title: Exclude KeyVault and KeyVaultCNG registry keys while exporting registry for DCT collection.

description:
[Remote Experience][CDR][iOS Client] Fix bug 2315689 - UI Option "File sharing" is not hidden when agent disables CDR

Issue
When CDR is disabled in agent side, the in-session settings still shows the CDR option, this is different from other clients.

Root Cause
The in-session settings can not be updated according to CDR client and agent capability negotiation after session connected.

Solution
Record the result of CDR client and agent capability negotiation after session connected, and update the in-session settings according to it

QA Notes: 
Testing Done: 
hcios

description:
[DPM-3230][hcwin]Unregister all file handlers before register new file handlers to make sure the removed entitlements disappear from the open with menu

Problem:
The file association handlers for the removed entitlements still exist in the open with popup menu.

Solution:
Using synchrounsly merging for App Management mode.
And remove the old file association handlers before registering new ones.
